name: 'Right Here' Special Bonus Edition - solo debut album
description:
*ALL PRICES SHOWN IN NEW ZEALAND DOLLARS*
please refer to the currency converter in the side bar

“The songs on ‘Right Here’ have come out of living here in Silver Lake, my slice of LA that I’ve made my home for the past couple of years. Some of the songs talk of the chronic themes of love, loving and loss. Some songs are stories of this city, some are of missing home and people.  And some talk of wanting something more for the world and everyone in it. But overall, these songs and this album come from my personal environment. They reflect me and the life I’m living in for the moment. They are grounded in, coloured and textured by being ‘Right Here’, now.”
Boh Runga

name: Fantail Hoop Earrings
description:
Boh Runga first captured our heartstrings four years ago with her inaugural and innovative ‘Birdland’ collection for the New Zealand Mint and now she adds to her first family of Birdland embellishments with her new collection of Birdland Charms & Hoop Earrings.

Fantail

In Maori Mythology, the cheeky little bird we know as the Fantail, Piwakawaka was one of the great Maui’s companions and one he would often take the form of. Fantails are fascinating to watch as they dart and play while looking for insects. Curious and comical, they make me smile.

name: Robin Hoop Earrings
description:
Boh Runga first captured our heartstrings four years ago with her inaugural and innovative ‘Birdland’ collection for the New Zealand Mint and now she adds to her first family of Birdland embellishments with her new collection of Birdland Charms & Hoop Earrings.

Robin
Once upon a time there were only 5 little Black Robins left in the world. Through dedicated conservation efforts, the Black Robin has had a miraculous comeback. From one female Black Robin called ‘Old Blue’ we are lucky to still have these birds in our incredible Birdland.

name: Tui Hoop Earrings
description:
Boh Runga first captured our heartstrings four years ago with her inaugural and innovative ‘Birdland’ collection for the New Zealand Mint and now she adds to her first family of Birdland embellishments with her new collection of Birdland Charms & Hoop Earrings.

Tui

In my garden back home in Auckland, every day I hear my resident ‘parsons bird’ or Tui. His strange, noisy calls bring me outside and I like to peer up into the surrounding trees to see where he is. He is so handsome, dressed in black with his flamboyant neckpiece. What a gentleman.

name: Kakapo Clip-on-Charm
description:
Boh Runga first captured our heartstrings four years ago with her inaugural and innovative ‘Birdland’ collection for the New Zealand Mint and now she adds to her first family of Birdland embellishments with her new collection of Birdland Charms & Hoop Earrings. Each individual charm is presented in a delightful organza bag with matching drawstring ribbon. 

Kakapo

The world’s rarest parrot, Aotearoa’s very own Kakapo. With less than 90 on the planet today, the Kakapo is staring extinction in the face. The Kakapo are said to smell like a musty combination of honey and flowers and their feathers are said to be incredibly downy soft. They are like something from a fairytale. The world will be a sadder place if we lose our Kakapo.

(Bracelet and charms sold separately)
